snippet.textDisplay:
The Baritone Poetry, The Classical Vocal on Yaman, Synchronized Kawali brothers, The touch of Violins, The aura of Chelo like faint moonbeams, The interlude of Sitar, The folk flavor of Dholak and jhumkis, The "Rock"y electronic guitar, The incredible fiery drumming from Ahad and the mystical melody of Quratulain Balouch...... and then there is  MAGIC ...spelbounding 8.30 mints .... 

SALAM and HUG to all musicians and arrangers individually...lots and lots of love from INDIA
snippet.textOriginal:
The Baritone Poetry, The Classical Vocal on Yaman, Synchronized Kawali brothers, The touch of Violins, The aura of Chelo like faint moonbeams, The interlude of Sitar, The folk flavor of Dholak and jhumkis, The "Rock"y electronic guitar, The incredible fiery drumming from Ahad and the mystical melody of Quratulain Balouch...... and then there is  MAGIC ...spelbounding 8.30 mints .... 

SALAM and HUG to all musicians and arrangers individually...lots and lots of love from INDIA
